quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
42,45,"You shall see them, as they are brought face to face with the chastisement, in a state of abject humiliation, looking with a furtive glance. {1} But the believers will say: “Surely the true losers are they who lose themselves and their kindred on the Day of Resurrection.” Lo, the wrong-doers will be in an enduring torment.",footnotes:1:By nature man is such that when a dreadful scene comes before him and he knows that soon he is going to fall a prey to it
42,46,"They shall have no protectors to help them against Allah. For he whom Allah causes to go astray will have no way to save himself."
42,47,"Accept the command of your Lord before there comes a Day from Allah that cannot be averted. {1} On that Day there shall be no shelter for you, and none may change your predicament. {2}",footnotes:1:That is
42,48,"(O Prophet), if they turn away from the Truth, know that We did not send you to them as their overseer. {1} Your task is only to convey (the Message). Indeed when We give man a taste of Our Mercy, he exults in it. But if any misfortune afflicts them on account of their deeds, man is utterly ungrateful. {2}",footnotes:1:That is
42,49,"The dominion of the heavens and the earth belongs to Allah. {1} He creates whatever He pleases. He grants females to whomever He pleases and males to whomever He pleases,",footnotes:1:That is
42,50,"or grants them a mix of males and females, and causes whomever He pleases to be barren. He is All- Knowing, All-Powerful. {1}",footnotes:1:This is a manifest proof of Allah’s Sovereignty being absolute. No man
42,51,"It {1} is not given to any human being that Allah should speak to him except through revelation, {2} or from behind a veil, {3} or that a messenger (an angel) be sent to him who reveals to him by Allah's leave whatever He wishes. {4} He is All-High, Most Wise. {5}",footnotes:1:In conclusion
